abstract: Two long-delayed New York-area rail projects received mixed reviews from federal officials Monday, as a plan for a replacement for a century-old bridge earned high enough marks to finally qualify for federal funding but a larger project to build a new tunnel under the Hudson River remained mired in a dispute over how much New York and New Jersey will pay.
snippet: Two long-delayed New York-area rail projects received mixed reviews from federal officials Monday, as a plan for a replacement for a century-old bridge earned high enough marks to finally qualify for federal funding but a larger project to build a...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Two long-delayed New York-area rail projects received mixed reviews from federal officials Monday, as a plan for a replacement for a century-old bridge earned high enough marks to finally qualify for federal funding but a larger project to build a new tunnel under the Hudson River remained mired in a dispute over how much New York and New Jersey will pay.
headline_main: Rail Bridge OK'd to Seek Fed Funds; Tunnel Doesn't Make Cut
headline_print_headline: Rail Bridge OK'd to Seek Fed Funds; Tunnel Doesn't Make Cut

headline_main: The Illness Now Has a Name, COVID-19

abstract: The president was in New Hampshire too, and so were his admirers.
snippet: The president was in New Hampshire too, and so were his admirers.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — President Trump spoke for an hour to an enthusiastic crowd of more than 11,000 at the Southern New Hampshire University Arena on Monday night under banners that read “Promises Made” and “Promises Kept.” Two nights earlier, this same venue hosted the New Hampshire Democratic Party’s 100 Club dinner.

abstract: President Trump’s former campaign adviser was convicted of lying to Congress and trying to block a witness in order to impede an investigation into the 2016 Trump campaign.
snippet: President Trump’s former campaign adviser was convicted of lying to Congress and trying to block a witness in order to impede an investigation into the 2016 Trump campaign.
lead_paragraph: Federal prosecutors asked a judge on Monday to sentence Roger J. Stone Jr., President Trump’s longtime friend and former campaign adviser, to up to nine years in prison for lying to Congress and tampering with a witness to prevent investigators from discovering how the 2016 Trump campaign tried to benefit from stolen Democratic documents.

abstract: The West Virginia Democrat, who dashed President Trump’s hopes for a bipartisan acquittal, said his vote to convict was not about politics.
snippet: The West Virginia Democrat, who dashed President Trump’s hopes for a bipartisan acquittal, said his vote to convict was not about politics.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Joe Manchin III votes with President Trump more than any other Democrat in the Senate. But his vote last week to convict Mr. Trump of impeachable offenses has eclipsed all of that, earning him the rage of a president who coveted a bipartisan acquittal.

abstract: President Donald Trump traveled Monday to Dover Air Force Base in Delaware to pay respects to two U.S. soldiers killed Saturday in Afghanistan when a soldier dressed in an Afghan army uniform opened fire with a machine gun.
snippet: President Donald Trump traveled Monday to Dover Air Force Base in Delaware to pay respects to two U.S. soldiers killed Saturday in Afghanistan when a soldier dressed in an Afghan army uniform opened fire with a machine gun.
lead_paragraph: DOVER AIR FORCE BASE, Del. — President Donald Trump traveled Monday to Dover Air Force Base in Delaware to pay respects to two U.S. soldiers killed Saturday in Afghanistan when a soldier dressed in an Afghan army uniform opened fire with a machine gun.
headline_main: Trump Pays Tribute to 2 Soldiers Killed in Afghanistan
headline_print_headline: Trump Pays Tribute to 2 Soldiers Killed in Afghanistan

abstract: The suits were an escalation of the Trump administration’s fight against laws that limit cooperation with federal immigration authorities.
snippet: The suits were an escalation of the Trump administration’s fight against laws that limit cooperation with federal immigration authorities.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Justice Department has sued local and state governments in California, New Jersey and Washington State as part of a “significant escalation” in the Trump administration’s fight against so-called sanctuary laws aimed at limiting cooperation with federal immigration authorities, Attorney General William P. Barr said on Monday.

abstract: On the eve of the state’s presidential primary, he arrived with a team of surrogates who will visit polling places on Tuesday.
snippet: On the eve of the state’s presidential primary, he arrived with a team of surrogates who will visit polling places on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — In his first rally since the Senate acquitted him on charges that he abused power and obstructed Congress, a triumphant President Trump returned on Monday to New Hampshire, the state where he won his first primary in 2016 and that he hopes to carry in 2020.
